channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: A Personalized Dense Retrieval Framework for Unified Information Access
item.description: Developing a universal model that can efficiently and effectively respond to a wide range of information access requests -- from retrieval to recommendation to question answering -- has been a long-lasting goal in the information retrieval community.

item.title: Video Frame Interpolation with Densely Queried Bilateral Correlation
item.description: To better model correlations and to produce more accurate motion fields, we propose the Densely Queried Bilateral Correlation (DQBC) that gets rid of the receptive field dependency problem and thus is more friendly to small and fast-moving objects.

item.title: ESPT: A Self-Supervised Episodic Spatial Pretext Task for Improving Few-Shot Learning
item.description: With this definition, the ESPT-augmented FSL objective promotes learning more transferable feature representations that capture the local spatial features of different images and their inter-relational structural information in each input episode, thus enabling the model to generalize better to new categories with only a few samples.

item.title: What Happened 3 Seconds Ago? Inferring the Past with Thermal Imaging
item.description: Inferring past human motion from RGB images is challenging due to the inherent uncertainty of the prediction problem.

item.title: Effect of latent space distribution on the segmentation of images with multiple annotations
item.description: We propose the Generalized Probabilistic U-Net, which extends the Probabilistic U-Net by allowing more general forms of the Gaussian distribution as the latent space distribution that can better approximate the uncertainty in the reference segmentations.

item.title: STIR: Siamese Transformer for Image Retrieval Postprocessing
item.description: Current metric learning approaches for image retrieval are usually based on learning a space of informative latent representations where simple approaches such as the cosine distance will work well.

item.title: A Control-Centric Benchmark for Video Prediction
item.description: Video is a promising source of knowledge for embodied agents to learn models of the world's dynamics.

item.title: Diffsurv: Differentiable sorting for censored time-to-event data
item.description: Additionally, we demonstrate the benefits of the algorithmic supervision enabled by Diffsurv by presenting a novel method for top-k risk prediction that outperforms current methods.

item.title: Domain Adaptive and Generalizable Network Architectures and Training Strategies for Semantic Image Segmentation
item.description: As previous UDA&DG semantic segmentation methods are mostly based on outdated networks, we benchmark more recent architectures, reveal the potential of Transformers, and design the DAFormer network tailored for UDA&DG.

item.title: Compensation Learning in Semantic Segmentation
item.description: In this paper, we propose Compensation Learning in Semantic Segmentation, a framework to identify and compensate ambiguities as well as label noise.

item.title: HiQ -- A Declarative, Non-intrusive, Dynamic and Transparent Observability and Optimization System
item.description: This paper proposes a non-intrusive, declarative, dynamic and transparent system called `HiQ` to track Python program runtime information without compromising on the run-time system performance and losing insight.

item.title: VGOS: Voxel Grid Optimization for View Synthesis from Sparse Inputs
item.description: In this paper, we propose VGOS, an approach for fast (3-5 minutes) radiance field reconstruction from sparse inputs (3-10 views) to address these issues.

item.title: Federated Learning with Uncertainty-Based Client Clustering for Fleet-Wide Fault Diagnosis
item.description: To quantify dataset similarity between clients without explicitly sharing data, each client sets aside a local test dataset and evaluates the other clients' model prediction accuracy and uncertainty on this test dataset.

item.title: Unleashing Infinite-Length Input Capacity for Large-scale Language Models with Self-Controlled Memory System
item.description: To address this limitation, we propose the Self-Controlled Memory (SCM) system to unleash infinite-length input capacity for large-scale language models.

item.title: Feed-Forward Optimization With Delayed Feedback for Neural Networks
item.description: Backpropagation has long been criticized for being biologically implausible, relying on concepts that are not viable in natural learning processes.

item.title: OpenBox: A Python Toolkit for Generalized Black-box Optimization
item.description: Black-box optimization (BBO) has a broad range of applications, including automatic machine learning, experimental design, and database knob tuning.

item.title: Efficient Explainable Face Verification based on Similarity Score Argument Backpropagation
item.description: Explainable Face Recognition is gaining growing attention as the use of the technology is gaining ground in security-critical applications.

item.title: Learnable Ophthalmology SAM
item.description: Based on Segment Anything (SAM), we propose a simple but effective learnable prompt layer suitable for multiple target segmentation in ophthalmology multi-modal images, named Learnable Ophthalmology Segment Anything (SAM).

item.title: SEAL: Simultaneous Label Hierarchy Exploration And Learning
item.description: Label hierarchy is an important source of external knowledge that can enhance classification performance.

item.title: HausaNLP at SemEval-2023 Task 12: Leveraging African Low Resource TweetData for Sentiment Analysis
item.description: We present the findings of SemEval-2023 Task 12, a shared task on sentiment analysis for low-resource African languages using Twitter dataset.

item.title: Reformulating CTR Prediction: Learning Invariant Feature Interactions for Recommendation
item.description: However, such a manner inevitably learns unstable feature interactions, i. e., the ones that exhibit strong correlations in historical data but generalize poorly for future serving.

item.title: Game-based Platforms for Artificial Intelligence Research
item.description: Games have been the perfect test-beds for artificial intelligence research for the characteristics that widely exist in real-world scenarios.

item.title: From Association to Generation: Text-only Captioning by Unsupervised Cross-modal Mapping
item.description: Although previous works have created generation capacity for CLIP through additional language models, a modality gap between the CLIP representations of different modalities and the inability of CLIP to model the offset of this gap, which fails the concept to transfer across modalities.

item.title: Stable and low-precision training for large-scale vision-language models
item.description: We introduce new methods for 1) accelerating and 2) stabilizing training for large language-vision models.

item.title: Uncovering the Representation of Spiking Neural Networks Trained with Surrogate Gradient
item.description: However, some essential questions exist pertaining to SNNs that are little studied: Do SNNs trained with surrogate gradient learn different representations from traditional Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs)?

item.title: Positive definite nonparametric regression using an evolutionary algorithm with application to covariance function estimation
item.description: We also extend our method to estimate covariance functions for point-referenced data.

item.title: Dynamic Datasets and Market Environments for Financial Reinforcement Learning
item.description: The financial market is a particularly challenging playground for deep reinforcement learning due to its unique feature of dynamic datasets.

item.title: Introducing MBIB -- the first Media Bias Identification Benchmark Task and Dataset Collection
item.description: A unified benchmark encourages the development of more robust systems and shifts the current paradigm in media bias detection evaluation towards solutions that tackle not one but multiple media bias types simultaneously.

item.title: Differential Privacy via Distributionally Robust Optimization
item.description: We show that the problem affords a strong dual, and we exploit this duality to develop converging hierarchies of finite-dimensional upper and lower bounding problems.

item.title: MixNeRF: Memory Efficient NeRF with Feature Mixed-up Hash Table
item.description: Neural radiance field (NeRF) has shown remarkable performance in generating photo-realistic novel views.

item.title: Class Attention Transfer Based Knowledge Distillation
item.description: Previous knowledge distillation methods have shown their impressive performance on model compression tasks, however, it is hard to explain how the knowledge they transferred helps to improve the performance of the student network.

item.title: Proto-Value Networks: Scaling Representation Learning with Auxiliary Tasks
item.description: Combined with a suitable off-policy learning rule, the result is a representation learning algorithm that can be understood as extending Mahadevan & Maggioni (2007)'s proto-value functions to deep reinforcement learning -- accordingly, we call the resulting object proto-value networks.

item.title: AdaNPC: Exploring Non-Parametric Classifier for Test-Time Adaptation
item.description: In particular, when the adaptation target is a series of domains, the adaptation accuracy of AdaNPC is 50% higher than advanced TTA methods.

item.title: THUIR at WSDM Cup 2023 Task 1: Unbiased Learning to Rank
item.description: This paper introduces the approaches we have used to participate in the WSDM Cup 2023 Task 1: Unbiased Learning to Rank.

item.title: Intent Induction from Conversations for Task-Oriented Dialogue Track at DSTC 11
item.description: With increasing demand for and adoption of virtual assistants, recent work has investigated ways to accelerate bot schema design through the automatic induction of intents or the induction of slots and dialogue states.

item.title: iMixer: hierarchical Hopfield network implies an invertible, implicit and iterative MLP-Mixer
item.description: In this paper we generalize the correspondence to the recently introduced hierarchical Hopfield network, and find iMixer, a novel generalization of MLP-Mixer model.

item.title: Change detection needs change information: improving deep 3D point cloud change detection
item.description: In particular, the last network, entitled Encoder Fusion SiamKPConv, overtakes SoTA with more than 5% of mean of IoU over classes of change emphasizing the value of having the network focus on change information for change detection task.

item.title: Application of Segment Anything Model for Civil Infrastructure Defect Assessment
item.description: In conclusion, the SAM and U-Net model presented in this study offer promising solutions for detecting cracks in concrete structures and leveraging the strengths of both models that can lead to more accurate and comprehensive results.

item.title: Morphological Classification of Extragalactic Radio Sources Using Gradient Boosting Methods
item.description: Most recent contributions in the field of morphological classification of extragalactic radio sources have proposed classifiers based on convolutional neural networks.

item.title: AI-assisted coding: Experiments with GPT-4
item.description: We report several experiments using GPT-4 to generate computer code.

item.title: Measuring Massive Multitask Chinese Understanding
item.description: This test encompasses four major domains, including medicine, law, psychology, and education, with 15 subtasks in medicine and 8 subtasks in education.

item.title: MG-ShopDial: A Multi-Goal Conversational Dataset for e-Commerce
item.description: To address this, we introduce MG-ShopDial: a dataset of conversations mixing different goals in the domain of e-commerce.

item.title: Weakly-Supervised Temporal Action Localization with Bidirectional Semantic Consistency Constraint
item.description: The proposed Bi-SCC firstly adopts a temporal context augmentation to generate an augmented video that breaks the correlation between positive actions and their co-scene actions in the inter-video; Then, a semantic consistency constraint (SCC) is used to enforce the predictions of the original video and augmented video to be consistent, hence suppressing the co-scene actions.

item.title: Proximal Curriculum for Reinforcement Learning Agents
item.description: We consider the problem of curriculum design for reinforcement learning (RL) agents in contextual multi-task settings.

item.title: Learnable Pillar-based Re-ranking for Image-Text Retrieval
item.description: Image-text retrieval aims to bridge the modality gap and retrieve cross-modal content based on semantic similarities.

item.title: Parallel Spiking Neurons with High Efficiency and Long-term Dependencies Learning Ability
item.description: Vanilla spiking neurons in Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) use charge-fire-reset neuronal dynamics, which can only be simulated in serial and can hardly learn long-time dependencies.

item.title: IMUPoser: Full-Body Pose Estimation using IMUs in Phones, Watches, and Earbuds
item.description: Tracking body pose on-the-go could have powerful uses in fitness, mobile gaming, context-aware virtual assistants, and rehabilitation.

item.title: (Local) Differential Privacy has NO Disparate Impact on Fairness
item.description: However, as the collection of multiple sensitive information becomes more prevalent across various industries, collecting a single sensitive attribute under LDP may not be sufficient.

item.title: Flickr-PAD: New Face High-Resolution Presentation Attack Detection Database
item.description: This will help researchers to compare new approaches to existing algorithms on a wider database.

item.title: DQS3D: Densely-matched Quantization-aware Semi-supervised 3D Detection
item.description: While this paradigm is natural for image-level or pixel-level prediction, adapting it to the detection problem is challenged by the issue of proposal matching.
